Philippine Stocks: San Miguel Corp., SM Prime Holdings Inc.

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-12T04:45:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/philippine-stocks-san-miguel-corp-sm-prime-holdings-inc-.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.7 percent to
4,199.48.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  , the  Philippines ’ biggest food
and beverage-maker, sank 4.4 percent to 153 pesos, a second day
of losses after the company announced a share sale plan. The
stock tumbled 7.5 percent yesterday after saying it and a
shareholder will sell $850 million of shares and convertible
bonds. San Miguel President Ramon Ang said in November the
company plans to raise $3 billion from the sale of common
shares.  “The market is disappointed because it seems the price of
the shares and the size of the proceeds will be lower than what
were indicated before,” said Peter Lee, senior investment
officer at Manila-based IGC Securities Inc. “It’s a sign that
there’s weak demand.”  SM Prime Holdings Inc. (SMPH)  , largest Philippine
shopping mall operator, fell 2 percent to 11.74 pesos, the
sharpest loss this month. The stock’s rating was lowered to
“hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank AG by analyst Carl Sy.
The brokerage has a 12-month share price estimate of 12.84 pesos  To contact the reporter on this story:
